May 20th, 2024
==============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.28.0): This release adds support for using Guardrails with Bedrock Agents.
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.28.0): This release adds support for using Guardrails with Bedrock Agents.
- `aws-sdk-controltower` (1.27.0): Added ListControlOperations API and filtering support for ListEnabledControls API. Updates also includes added metadata for enabled controls and control operations.
- `aws-sdk-osis` (1.26.0): Add support for creating an OpenSearch Ingestion pipeline that is attached to a provided VPC. Add information about the destinations of an OpenSearch Ingestion pipeline to the GetPipeline and ListPipelines APIs.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.35.0): This release adds support for EngineLifecycleSupport on DBInstances, DBClusters, and GlobalClusters.
- `aws-sdk-secretsmanager` (1.28.0): add v2 smoke tests and smithy smokeTests trait for SDK testing

May 17th, 2024
==============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-applicationautoscaling` (1.27.0): add v2 smoke tests and smithy smokeTests trait for SDK testing.
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.33.0): Aws CodeBuild now supports 36 hours build timeout
- `aws-sdk-elasticloadbalancingv2` (1.27.0): This release adds dualstack-without-public-ipv4 IP address type for ALB.
- `aws-sdk-lakeformation` (1.28.0): Introduces a new API, GetDataLakePrincipal, that returns the identity of the invoking principal
- `aws-sdk-transfer` (1.29.0): Enable use of CloudFormation traits in Smithy model to improve generated CloudFormation schema from the Smithy API model.

May 16th, 2024
==============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-acmpca` (1.26.0): This release adds support for waiters to fail on AccessDeniedException when having insufficient permissions
- `aws-sdk-kafka` (1.27.0): AWS MSK support for Broker Removal.
- `aws-sdk-mwaa` (1.28.0): Amazon MWAA now supports Airflow web server auto scaling to automatically handle increased demand from REST APIs, Command Line Interface (CLI), or more Airflow User Interface (UI) users. Customers can specify maximum and minimum web server instances during environment creation and update workflow.
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.32.0): This release adds DescribeKeyRegistration and UpdateKeyRegistration APIs to manage QuickSight Customer Managed Keys (CMK).
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.43.0): Introduced WorkerAccessConfiguration to SageMaker Workteam. This allows customers to configure resource access for workers in a workteam.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-connect` (1.38.1): Adding Contact Flow metrics to the GetMetricDataV2 API
- `aws-sdk-secretsmanager` (1.27.1): Documentation updates for AWS Secrets Manager

May 15th, 2024
==============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.27.0): Updating Bedrock Knowledge Base Metadata & Filters feature with two new filters listContains and stringContains
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.32.0): CodeBuild Reserved Capacity VPC Support
- `aws-sdk-datasync` (1.28.0): Task executions now display a CANCELLING status when an execution is in the process of being cancelled.
- `aws-sdk-grafana` (1.27.0): This release adds new ServiceAccount and ServiceAccountToken APIs.
- `aws-sdk-medicalimaging` (1.27.0): Added support for importing medical imaging data from Amazon S3 buckets across accounts and regions.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-securityhub` (1.27.1): Documentation-only update for AWS Security Hub

May 13th, 2024
==============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-eventbridge` (1.25.0): Amazon EventBridge introduces KMS customer-managed key (CMK) encryption support for custom and partner events published on EventBridge Event Bus (including default bus) and UpdateEventBus API.
- `aws-sdk-vpclattice` (1.25.0): This release adds TLS Passthrough support. It also increases max number of target group per rule to 10.

May 10th, 2024
==============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-applicationdiscovery` (1.25.0): add v2 smoke tests and smithy smokeTests trait for SDK testing
- `aws-sdk-greengrassv2` (1.25.0): Mark ComponentVersion in ComponentDeploymentSpecification as required.
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.41.0): Introduced support for G6 instance types on Sagemaker Notebook Instances and on SageMaker Studio for JupyterLab and CodeEditor applications.
- `aws-sdk-ssooidc` (1.25.0): Updated request parameters for PKCE support.

May 9th, 2024
=============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.25.0): This release adds support to provide guardrail configuration and modify inference parameters that are then used in RetrieveAndGenerate API in Agents for Amazon Bedrock.
- `aws-sdk-pinpoint` (1.26.0): This release adds support for specifying email message headers for Email Templates, Campaigns, Journeys and Send Messages.
- `aws-sdk-ssmsap` (1.25.0): Added support for application-aware start/stop of SAP applications running on EC2 instances, with SSM for SAP
- `aws-sdk-verifiedpermissions` (1.29.0): Adds policy effect and actions fields to Policy API's.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-route53resolver` (1.27.1): Update the DNS Firewall settings to correct a spelling issue.

May 8th, 2024
=============
**Breaking Changes:**
- :warning::tada: ([smithy-rs#3527](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3527)) Stalled stream protection on uploads is now enabled by default behind `BehaviorVersion::v2024_03_28()`. If you're using `BehaviorVersion::latest()`, you will get this change automatically by running `cargo update`. Updating your SDK is not necessary, this change will happen when a new version of the client libraries are consumed.

**New this release:**
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3427](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3427)) `aws-config::loader::ConfigLoader` now creates an `IdentityCache` by default when using `BehaviorVersion::v2024_03_28()`
    or newer. If you're using `BehaviorVersion::latest()`, you will get this change automatically when updating. This
    allows clients created from `SdkConfig` to use the same cache instance by default resulting in fewer cache misses
    when using multiple clients.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cognitoidentityprovider` (1.28.0): Add EXTERNAL_PROVIDER enum value to UserStatusType.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.41.0): Adding Precision Hardware Clock (PHC) to public API DescribeInstanceTypes
- `aws-sdk-ecr` (1.24.0): This release adds pull through cache rules support for GitLab container registry in Amazon ECR.
- `aws-sdk-polly` (1.25.0): Add new engine - generative - that builds the most expressive conversational voices.
- `aws-sdk-sqs` (1.24.0): This release adds MessageSystemAttributeNames to ReceiveMessageRequest to replace AttributeNames.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-fms` (1.26.0): The policy scope resource tag is always a string value, either a non-empty string or an empty string.

May 7th, 2024
=============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-budgets` (1.23.0): This release adds tag support for budgets and budget actions.
- `aws-sdk-resiliencehub` (1.23.0): AWS Resilience Hub has expanded its drift detection capabilities by introducing a new type of drift detection - application resource drift. This new enhancement detects changes, such as the addition or deletion of resources within the application's input sources.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-b2bi` (1.23.0): Documentation update to clarify the MappingTemplate definition.
- `aws-sdk-route53profiles` (1.2.0): Doc only update for Route 53 profiles that fixes some link  issues

May 6th, 2024
=============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-medialive` (1.28.0): AWS Elemental MediaLive now supports configuring how SCTE 35 passthrough triggers segment breaks in HLS and MediaPackage output groups. Previously, messages triggered breaks in all these output groups. The new option is to trigger segment breaks only in groups that have SCTE 35 passthrough enabled.

May 3rd, 2024
=============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.24.0): This release adds support for using Provisioned Throughput with Bedrock Agents.
- `aws-sdk-connect` (1.35.0): This release adds 5 new APIs for managing attachments: StartAttachedFileUpload, CompleteAttachedFileUpload, GetAttachedFile, BatchGetAttachedFileMetadata, DeleteAttachedFile. These APIs can be used to programmatically upload and download attachments to Connect resources, like cases.
- `aws-sdk-connectcases` (1.25.0): This feature supports the release of Files related items
- `aws-sdk-inspector2` (1.26.0): This release adds CSV format to GetCisScanReport for Inspector v2
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.38.0): Amazon SageMaker Inference now supports m6i, c6i, r6i, m7i, c7i, r7i and g5 instance types for Batch Transform Jobs
- `aws-sdk-sesv2` (1.24.0): Adds support for specifying replacement headers per BulkEmailEntry in SendBulkEmail in SESv2.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-datasync` (1.24.1): Updated guidance on using private or self-signed certificate authorities (CAs) with AWS DataSync object storage locations.

May 2nd, 2024
=============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-dynamodb` (1.25.0): This release adds support to specify an optional, maximum OnDemandThroughput for DynamoDB tables and global secondary indexes in the CreateTable or UpdateTable APIs. You can also override the OnDemandThroughput settings by calling the ImportTable, RestoreFromPointInTime, or RestoreFromBackup APIs.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.39.0): This release includes a new API for retrieving the public endorsement key of the EC2 instance's Nitro Trusted Platform Module (NitroTPM).
- `aws-sdk-personalize` (1.24.0): This releases ability to delete users and their data, including their metadata and interactions data, from a dataset group.
- `aws-sdk-redshiftserverless` (1.24.0): Update Redshift Serverless List Scheduled Actions Output Response to include Namespace Name.

May 1st, 2024
=============
**New this release:**
- :tada: ([aws-sdk-rust#400](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/400), [smithy-rs#3595](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3595), [smithy-rs#3593](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3593), [smithy-rs#3585](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3585), [smithy-rs#3571](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3571), [smithy-rs#3569](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3569)) Added support for waiters. Services that model waiters now have a `Waiters` trait that adds
    some methods prefixed with `wait_until` to the existing clients. These can be used to, for example
    in S3, wait for a newly created bucket to be ready, or in EC2, to wait for a started instance to
    have the status OK.

    Using a waiter looks like the following example for EC2:
    ```rust
    use aws_sdk_ec2::client::Waiters;

    let result = ec2_client.wait_until_instance_status_ok()
        .instance_ids("some-instance-id")
        .wait(Duration::from_secs(300))
        .await;
    ```
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3601](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3601)) SDK crates now set the `rust-version` property in their Cargo.toml files to indicate the minimum supported Rust version.
- ([aws-sdk-rust#879](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/879), [smithy-rs#3611](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3611)) `aws_config::default_provider::use_dual_stack_provider` is now public instead of `pub(crate)`

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.23.0): This release adds support for using MongoDB Atlas as a vector store when creating a knowledge base.
- `aws-sdk-personalizeruntime` (1.22.0): This release adds support for a Reason attribute for predicted items generated by User-Personalization-v2.
- `aws-sdk-securityhub` (1.24.0): Updated CreateMembers API request with limits.
- `aws-sdk-sesv2` (1.23.0): Fixes ListContacts and ListImportJobs APIs to use POST instead of GET.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.38.0): Documentation updates for Amazon EC2.

April 30th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-chimesdkvoice` (1.22.0): Due to changes made by the Amazon Alexa service, GetSipMediaApplicationAlexaSkillConfiguration and PutSipMediaApplicationAlexaSkillConfiguration APIs are no longer available for use. For more information, refer to the Alexa Smart Properties page.
- `aws-sdk-codeartifact` (1.23.0): Add support for the Ruby package format.
- `aws-sdk-fms` (1.23.0): AWS Firewall Manager now supports the network firewall service stream exception policy feature for accounts within your organization.
- `aws-sdk-omics` (1.23.0): Add support for workflow sharing and dynamic run storage
- `aws-sdk-opensearch` (1.26.0): This release enables customers to create Route53 A and AAAA alias record types to point custom endpoint domain to OpenSearch domain's dualstack search endpoint.
- `aws-sdk-pinpointsmsvoicev2` (1.22.0): Amazon Pinpoint has added two new features Multimedia services (MMS) and protect configurations. Use the three new MMS APIs to send media messages to a mobile phone which includes image, audio, text, or video files. Use the ten new protect configurations APIs to block messages to specific countries.
- `aws-sdk-qbusiness` (1.21.0): This is a general availability (GA) release of Amazon Q Business. Q Business enables employees in an enterprise to get comprehensive answers to complex questions and take actions through a unified, intuitive web-based chat experience - using an enterprise's existing content, data, and systems.
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.27.0): New Q embedding supporting Generative Q&A
- `aws-sdk-route53resolver` (1.24.0): Release of FirewallDomainRedirectionAction parameter on the Route 53 DNS Firewall Rule.  This allows customers to configure a DNS Firewall rule to inspect all the domains in the DNS redirection chain (default) , such as CNAME, ALIAS, DNAME, etc., or just the first domain and trust the rest.
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.36.0): Amazon SageMaker Training now supports the use of attribute-based access control (ABAC) roles for training job execution roles. Amazon SageMaker Inference now supports G6 instance types.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-signer` (1.21.1): Documentation updates for AWS Signer. Adds cross-account signing constraint and definitions for cross-account actions.

April 29th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-amplify` (1.23.0): Updating max results limit for listing any resources (Job, Artifacts, Branch, BackendResources, DomainAssociation) to 50 with the exception of list apps that where max results can be up to 100.
- `aws-sdk-connectcases` (1.23.0): This feature releases DeleteField, DeletedLayout, and DeleteTemplate API's
- `aws-sdk-inspector2` (1.24.0): Update Inspector2 to include new Agentless API parameters.
- `aws-sdk-timestreamquery` (1.22.0): This change allows users to update and describe account settings associated with their accounts.
- `aws-sdk-transcribe` (1.22.0): This update provides error messaging for generative call summarization in Transcribe Call Analytics
- `aws-sdk-trustedadvisor` (1.22.0): This release adds the BatchUpdateRecommendationResourceExclusion API to support batch updates of Recommendation Resource exclusion statuses and introduces a new exclusion status filter to the ListRecommendationResources and ListOrganizationRecommendationResources APIs.

April 26th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-codepipeline` (1.23.0): Add ability to manually and automatically roll back a pipeline stage to a previously successful execution.
- `aws-sdk-cognitoidentityprovider` (1.25.0): Add LimitExceededException to SignUp errors
- `aws-sdk-connectcampaigns` (1.23.0): This release adds support for specifying if Answering Machine should wait for prompt sound.
- `aws-sdk-marketplaceentitlement` (1.22.0): Releasing minor endpoint updates.
- `aws-sdk-oam` (1.23.0): This release introduces support for Source Accounts to define which Metrics and Logs to share with the Monitoring Account
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.30.0): SupportsLimitlessDatabase field added to describe-db-engine-versions to indicate whether the DB engine version supports Aurora Limitless Database.
- `aws-sdk-support` (1.22.0): Releasing minor endpoint updates.

April 25th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-appsync` (1.25.0): UpdateGraphQLAPI documentation update and datasource introspection secret arn update
- `aws-sdk-fms` (1.22.0): AWS Firewall Manager adds support for network ACL policies to manage Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) network access control lists (ACLs) for accounts in your organization.
- `aws-sdk-ivs` (1.24.0): Bug Fix: IVS does not support arns with the `svs` prefix
- `aws-sdk-ivsrealtime` (1.22.0): Bug Fix: IVS Real Time does not support ARNs using the `svs` prefix.
- `aws-sdk-sfn` (1.22.0): Add new ValidateStateMachineDefinition operation, which performs syntax checking on the definition of a Amazon States Language (ASL) state machine.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.29.2): Updates Amazon RDS documentation for setting local time zones for RDS for Db2 DB instances.

April 24th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-datasync` (1.23.0): This change allows users to disable and enable the schedules associated with their tasks.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.37.0): Launching capability for customers to enable or disable automatic assignment of public IPv4 addresses to their network interface
- `aws-sdk-emrcontainers` (1.24.0): EMRonEKS Service support for SecurityConfiguration enforcement for Spark Jobs.
- `aws-sdk-entityresolution` (1.23.0): Support Batch Unique IDs Deletion.
- `aws-sdk-gamelift` (1.22.0): Amazon GameLift releases container fleets support for public preview. Deploy Linux-based containerized game server software for hosting on Amazon GameLift.
- `aws-sdk-ssm` (1.24.0): Add SSM DescribeInstanceProperties API to public AWS SDK.

April 23rd, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrock` (1.23.0): This release introduces Model Evaluation and Guardrails for Amazon Bedrock.
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.22.0): Introducing the ability to create multiple data sources per knowledge base, specify S3 buckets as data sources from external accounts, and exposing levers to define the deletion behavior of the underlying vector store data.
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.21.0): This release introduces zero-setup file upload support for the RetrieveAndGenerate API. This allows you to chat with your data without setting up a Knowledge Base.
- `aws-sdk-bedrockruntime` (1.23.0): This release introduces Guardrails for Amazon Bedrock.
- `aws-sdk-costexplorer` (1.23.0): Added additional metadata that might be applicable to your reservation recommendations.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.36.0): This release introduces EC2 AMI Deregistration Protection, a new AMI property that can be enabled by customers to protect an AMI against an unintended deregistration. This release also enables the AMI owners to view the AMI 'LastLaunchedTime' in DescribeImages API.
- `aws-sdk-workspacesweb` (1.22.0): Added InstanceType and MaxConcurrentSessions parameters on CreatePortal and UpdatePortal Operations as well as the ability to read Customer Managed Key & Additional Encryption Context parameters on supported resources (Portal, BrowserSettings, UserSettings, IPAccessSettings)

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-pi` (1.21.1): Clarifies how aggregation works for GetResourceMetrics in the Performance Insights API.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.29.1): Fix the example ARN for ModifyActivityStreamRequest

April 22nd, 2024
================
**New this release:**
- ([smithy-rs#3553](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3553)) Upgraded MSRV to Rust 1.75
- ([smithy-rs#3533](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3533), @avandesa) Make `SigningSettings` and its fields implement `Clone` and `Copy`
- ([smithy-rs#3546](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3546), @orf) Change some credentials related info log messages to debug.
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3590](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3590), [aws-sdk-rust#1131](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1131)) Fix an S3 crate's dependency on `ahash` so the crate can be compiled for `wasm32-unknown-unknown`.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.21.0): Releasing the support for simplified configuration and return of control
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.20.0): Releasing the support for simplified configuration and return of control
- `aws-sdk-paymentcryptography` (1.23.0): Adding support to TR-31/TR-34 exports for optional headers, allowing customers to add additional metadata (such as key version and KSN) when exporting keys from the service.
- `aws-sdk-route53profiles` (1.0.0): Route 53 Profiles allows you to apply a central DNS configuration across many VPCs regardless of account.
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.35.0): This release adds support for Real-Time Collaboration and Shared Space for JupyterLab App on SageMaker Studio.
- `aws-sdk-transfer` (1.24.0): Adding new API to support remote directory listing using SFTP connector

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-redshiftserverless` (1.22.0): Updates description of schedule field for scheduled actions.
- `aws-sdk-servicediscovery` (1.21.0): This release adds examples to several Cloud Map actions.

**Contributors**
Thank you for your contributions! ❤
- @avandesa ([smithy-rs#3533](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3533))
- @orf ([smithy-rs#3546](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3546))

April 19th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-glue` (1.26.0): Adding RowFilter in the response for GetUnfilteredTableMetadata API
- `aws-sdk-internetmonitor` (1.23.0): This update introduces the GetInternetEvent and ListInternetEvents APIs, which provide access to internet events displayed on the Amazon CloudWatch Internet Weather Map.
- `aws-sdk-personalize` (1.21.0): This releases auto training capability while creating a solution and automatically syncing latest solution versions when creating/updating a campaign

April 18th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-drs` (1.23.0): Outpost ARN added to Source Server and Recovery Instance
- `aws-sdk-emrserverless` (1.22.0): This release adds the capability to publish detailed Spark engine metrics to Amazon Managed Service for Prometheus (AMP) for  enhanced monitoring for Spark jobs.
- `aws-sdk-guardduty` (1.24.0): Added IPv6Address fields for local and remote IP addresses
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.25.0): This release adds support for the Cross Sheet Filter and Control features, and support for warnings in asset imports for any permitted errors encountered during execution
- `aws-sdk-rolesanywhere` (1.23.0): This release introduces the PutAttributeMapping and DeleteAttributeMapping APIs. IAM Roles Anywhere now provides the capability to define a set of mapping rules, allowing customers to specify which data is extracted from their X.509 end-entity certificates.
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.34.0): Removed deprecated enum values and updated API documentation.
- `aws-sdk-workspaces` (1.21.0): Adds new APIs for managing and sharing WorkSpaces BYOL configuration across accounts.

April 16th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.20.0): For Create Agent API, the agentResourceRoleArn parameter is no longer required.
- `aws-sdk-emrserverless` (1.21.0): This release adds support for shuffle optimized disks that allow larger disk sizes and higher IOPS to efficiently run shuffle heavy workloads.
- `aws-sdk-entityresolution` (1.21.0): Cross Account Resource Support .
- `aws-sdk-iotwireless` (1.22.0): Add PublicGateways in the GetWirelessStatistics call response, indicating the LoRaWAN public network accessed by the device.
- `aws-sdk-lakeformation` (1.22.0): This release adds Lake Formation managed RAM support for the 4 APIs - "DescribeLakeFormationIdentityCenterConfiguration", "CreateLakeFormationIdentityCenterConfiguration", "DescribeLakeFormationIdentityCenterConfiguration", and "DeleteLakeFormationIdentityCenterConfiguration"
- `aws-sdk-m2` (1.21.0): Adding new ListBatchJobRestartPoints API and support for restart batch job.
- `aws-sdk-mediapackagev2` (1.22.0): Dash v2 is a MediaPackage V2 feature to support egressing on DASH manifest format.
- `aws-sdk-outposts` (1.22.0): This release adds new APIs to allow customers to configure their Outpost capacity at order-time.
- `aws-sdk-wellarchitected` (1.21.0): AWS Well-Architected now has a Connector for Jira to allow customers to efficiently track workload risks and improvement efforts and create closed-loop mechanisms.

April 12th, 2024
================
**New this release:**
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3485](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3485)) Stalled stream protection now supports request upload streams. It is currently off by default, but will be enabled by default in a future release. To enable it now, you can do the following:

    ```rust
    let config = aws_config::defaults(BehaviorVersion::latest())
        .stalled_stream_protection(StalledStreamProtectionConfig::enabled().build())
        .load()
        .await;
    ```
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3427](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3427)) Fixes the identity resolver types (`credentials_provider()` and `token_provider()`) from `SdkConfig` to have
    a consistent identity cache partition when re-used across different clients.
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3485](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3485)) Stalled stream protection on downloads will now only trigger if the upstream source is too slow. Previously, stalled stream protection could be erroneously triggered if the user was slowly consuming the stream slower than the minimum speed limit.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudformation` (1.25.0): Adding support for the new parameter "IncludePropertyValues" in the CloudFormation DescribeChangeSet API. When this parameter is included, the DescribeChangeSet response will include more detailed information such as before and after values for the resource properties that will change.
- `aws-sdk-glue` (1.25.0): Modifying request for GetUnfilteredTableMetadata for view-related fields.
- `aws-sdk-healthlake` (1.21.0): Added new CREATE_FAILED status for data stores. Added new errorCause to DescribeFHIRDatastore API and ListFHIRDatastores API response for additional insights into data store creation and deletion workflows.
- `aws-sdk-kms` (1.21.0): This feature supports the ability to specify a custom rotation period for automatic key rotations, the ability to perform on-demand key rotations, and visibility into your key material rotations.
- `aws-sdk-mediatailor` (1.22.0): Added InsertionMode to PlaybackConfigurations. This setting controls whether players can use stitched or guided ad insertion. The default for players that do not specify an insertion mode is stitched.
- `aws-sdk-outposts` (1.21.0): This release adds EXPEDITORS as a valid shipment carrier.
- `aws-sdk-redshift` (1.21.0): Adds support for Amazon Redshift DescribeClusterSnapshots API to include Snapshot ARN response field.
- `aws-sdk-transfer` (1.23.0): This change releases support for importing self signed certificates to the Transfer Family for sending outbound file transfers over TLS/HTTPS.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-config` (1.21.0): Updates documentation for AWS Config
- `aws-sdk-iotfleethub` (1.20.0): Documentation updates for AWS IoT Fleet Hub to clarify that Fleet Hub supports organization instance of IAM Identity Center.
- `aws-sdk-neptunegraph` (1.17.0): Update to API documentation to resolve customer reported issues.

April 11th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-batch` (1.24.0): This release adds the task properties field to attempt details and the name field on EKS container detail.
- `aws-sdk-cloudfront` (1.20.0): CloudFront origin access control extends support to AWS Lambda function URLs and AWS Elemental MediaPackage v2 origins.
- `aws-sdk-cloudwatch` (1.23.0): This release adds support for Metric Characteristics for CloudWatch Anomaly Detection. Anomaly Detector now takes Metric Characteristics object with Periodic Spikes boolean field that tells Anomaly Detection that spikes that repeat at the same time every week are part of the expected pattern.
- `aws-sdk-iam` (1.20.0): For CreateOpenIDConnectProvider API, the ThumbprintList parameter is no longer required.
- `aws-sdk-medialive` (1.24.0): AWS Elemental MediaLive introduces workflow monitor, a new feature that enables the visualization and monitoring of your media workflows. Create signal maps of your existing workflows and monitor them by creating notification and monitoring template groups.
- `aws-sdk-omics` (1.20.0): This release adds support for retrieval of S3 direct access metadata on sequence stores and read sets, and adds support for SHA256up and SHA512up HealthOmics ETags.
- `aws-sdk-pipes` (1.20.0): LogConfiguration ARN validation fixes
- `aws-sdk-wafv2` (1.23.0): Adds an updated version of smoke tests, including smithy trait, for SDK testing.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.25.1): Support access tokens for Bitbucket sources
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.27.1): Updates Amazon RDS documentation for Standard Edition 2 support in RDS Custom for Oracle.
- `aws-sdk-s3control` (1.21.1): Documentation updates for Amazon S3-control.

April 10th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cleanrooms` (1.22.0): AWS Clean Rooms Differential Privacy is now fully available. Differential privacy protects against user-identification attempts.
- `aws-sdk-connect` (1.31.0): This release adds new Submit Auto Evaluation Action for Amazon Connect Rules.
- `aws-sdk-qconnect` (1.21.0): This release adds a new QiC public API updateSession and updates an existing QiC public API createSession
- `aws-sdk-rekognition` (1.21.0): Added support for ContentType to content moderation detections.
- `aws-sdk-supplychain` (1.10.0): This release includes API SendDataIntegrationEvent for AWS Supply Chain
- `aws-sdk-workspacesthinclient` (1.19.0): Adding tags field to SoftwareSet. Removing tags fields from Summary objects. Changing the list of exceptions in tagging APIs. Fixing an issue where the SDK returns empty tags in Get APIs.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-networkmonitor` (1.10.1): Examples were added to CloudWatch Network Monitor commands.

April 9th, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.25.0): Add new webhook filter types for GitHub webhooks
- `aws-sdk-mediaconvert` (1.22.0): This release includes support for bringing your own fonts to use for burn-in or DVB-Sub captioning workflows.
- `aws-sdk-pinpoint` (1.20.0): The OrchestrationSendingRoleArn has been added to the email channel and is used to send emails from campaigns or journeys.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.27.0): This release adds support for specifying the CA certificate to use for the new db instance when restoring from db snapshot, restoring from s3, restoring to point in time, and creating a db instance read replica.

April 8th, 2024
===============
**Breaking Changes:**
- :bug::warning: ([aws-sdk-rust#1111](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1111), [smithy-rs#3513](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3513), @Ten0) Make `BehaviorVersion` be future-proof by disallowing it to be constructed via the `BehaviorVersion {}` syntax.

**New this release:**
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3506](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3506), @mokhaled2992) Ability to add an inline policy or a list of policy ARNs to the `WebIdentityTokenCredentialsProvider` builder.
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3493](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3493)) Users may now set service-specific configuration in the environment. For more information, see [this discussion topic](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/discussions/3537).
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3539](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3539)) Add FIPS support to our Hyper 1.0-based client. Customers can enable this mode by enabling the `crypto-aws-lc-fips` on `aws-smithy-experimental`. To construct a client using the new client, consult this [example](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/blob/release-2024-03-29/sdk/s3/tests/hyper-10.rs).

    Please note that support for Hyper 1.0 remains experimental.
- ([smithy-rs#3389](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3389)) All requests are now retryable, even if they are deserialized successfully. Previously, this was not allowed.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-controlcatalog` (1.0.0): This is the initial SDK release for AWS Control Catalog, a central catalog for AWS managed controls. This release includes 3 new APIs - ListDomains, ListObjectives, and ListCommonControls - that vend high-level data to categorize controls across the AWS platform.
- `aws-sdk-mgn` (1.19.0): Added USE_SOURCE as default option to LaunchConfigurationTemplate bootMode parameter.
- `aws-sdk-networkmonitor` (1.10.0): Updated the allowed monitorName length for CloudWatch Network Monitor.

**Contributors**
Thank you for your contributions! ❤
- @Ten0 ([aws-sdk-rust#1111](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1111), [smithy-rs#3513](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3513))

April 5th, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.22.0): Adding IAMIdentityCenterInstanceArn parameter to CreateAccountSubscription
- `aws-sdk-resourcegroups` (1.19.0): Added a new QueryErrorCode RESOURCE_TYPE_NOT_SUPPORTED that is returned by the ListGroupResources operation if the group query contains unsupported resource types.
- `aws-sdk-verifiedpermissions` (1.22.0): Adding BatchIsAuthorizedWithToken API which supports multiple authorization requests against a PolicyStore given a bearer token.

April 4th, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-b2bi` (1.18.0): Adding support for X12 5010 HIPAA EDI version and associated transaction sets.
- `aws-sdk-cleanrooms` (1.20.0): Feature: New schemaStatusDetails field to the existing Schema object that displays a status on Schema API responses to show whether a schema is queryable or not. New BatchGetSchemaAnalysisRule API to retrieve multiple schemaAnalysisRules using a single API call.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.31.0): Amazon EC2 G6 instances powered by NVIDIA L4 Tensor Core GPUs can be used for a wide range of graphics-intensive and machine learning use cases. Gr6 instances also feature NVIDIA L4 GPUs and can be used for graphics workloads with higher memory requirements.
- `aws-sdk-emrcontainers` (1.20.0): This release adds support for integration with EKS AccessEntry APIs to enable automatic Cluster Access for EMR on EKS.
- `aws-sdk-ivs` (1.20.0): API update to include an SRT ingest endpoint and passphrase for all channels.
- `aws-sdk-verifiedpermissions` (1.21.0): Adds GroupConfiguration field to Identity Source API's

April 3rd, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cleanroomsml` (1.16.0): The release includes a public SDK for AWS Clean Rooms ML APIs, making them globally available to developers worldwide.
- `aws-sdk-cloudformation` (1.23.0): This release would return a new field - PolicyAction in cloudformation's existed DescribeChangeSetResponse, showing actions we are going to apply on the physical resource (e.g., Delete, Retain) according to the user's template
- `aws-sdk-datazone` (1.21.0): This release supports the feature of dataQuality to enrich asset with dataQualityResult in Amazon DataZone.
- `aws-sdk-docdb` (1.20.0): This release adds Global Cluster Switchover capability which enables you to change your global cluster's primary AWS Region, the region that serves writes, while preserving the replication between all regions in the global cluster.
- `aws-sdk-groundstation` (1.19.0): This release adds visibilityStartTime and visibilityEndTime to DescribeContact and ListContacts responses.
- `aws-sdk-lambda` (1.19.0): Add Ruby 3.3 (ruby3.3) support to AWS Lambda
- `aws-sdk-medialive` (1.22.0): Cmaf Ingest outputs are now supported in Media Live
- `aws-sdk-medicalimaging` (1.19.0): SearchImageSets API now supports following enhancements - Additional support for searching on UpdatedAt and SeriesInstanceUID - Support for searching existing filters between dates/times - Support for sorting the search result by Ascending/Descending - Additional parameters returned in the response
- `aws-sdk-transfer` (1.21.0): Add ability to specify Security Policies for SFTP Connectors

April 2nd, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-glue` (1.23.0): Adding View related fields to responses of read-only Table APIs.
- `aws-sdk-rolesanywhere` (1.20.0): This release increases the limit on the roleArns request parameter for the *Profile APIs that support it. This parameter can now take up to 250 role ARNs.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.19.1): Documentation only update for Amazon ECS.
- `aws-sdk-ivschat` (1.18.1): Doc-only update. Changed "Resources" to "Key Concepts" in docs and updated text.
- `aws-sdk-securityhub` (1.20.1): Documentation updates for AWS Security Hub

April 1st, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudwatch` (1.21.0): This release adds support for CloudWatch Anomaly Detection on cross-account metrics. SingleMetricAnomalyDetector and MetricDataQuery inputs to Anomaly Detection APIs now take an optional AccountId field.
- `aws-sdk-datazone` (1.20.0): This release supports the feature of AI recommendations for descriptions to enrich the business data catalog in Amazon DataZone.
- `aws-sdk-deadline` (1.0.0): AWS Deadline Cloud is a new fully managed service that helps customers set up, deploy, and scale rendering projects in minutes, so they can improve the efficiency of their rendering pipelines and take on more projects.
- `aws-sdk-lightsail` (1.21.0): This release adds support to upgrade the TLS version of the distribution.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-emr` (1.20.1): This release fixes a broken link in the documentation.

March 29th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-b2bi` (1.17.0): Supporting new EDI X12 transaction sets for X12 versions 4010, 4030, and 5010.
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.23.0): Add new fleet status code for Reserved Capacity.
- `aws-sdk-codeconnections` (1.0.0): Duplicating the CodeStar Connections service into the new, rebranded AWS CodeConnections service.
- `aws-sdk-internetmonitor` (1.20.0): This release adds support to allow customers to track cross account monitors through ListMonitor, GetMonitor, ListHealthEvents, GetHealthEvent, StartQuery APIs.
- `aws-sdk-iotwireless` (1.19.0): Add support for retrieving key historical and live metrics for LoRaWAN devices and gateways
- `aws-sdk-marketplacecatalog` (1.22.0): This release enhances the ListEntities API to support ResaleAuthorizationId filter and sort for OfferEntity in the request and the addition of a ResaleAuthorizationId field in the response of OfferSummary.
- `aws-sdk-neptunegraph` (1.15.0): Add the new API Start-Import-Task for Amazon Neptune Analytics.
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.31.0): This release adds support for custom images for the CodeEditor App on SageMaker Studio

March 28th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-codecatalyst` (1.19.0): This release adds support for understanding pending changes to subscriptions by including two new response parameters for the GetSubscription API for Amazon CodeCatalyst.
- `aws-sdk-computeoptimizer` (1.19.0): This release enables AWS Compute Optimizer to analyze and generate recommendations with a new customization preference, Memory Utilization.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.30.0): Amazon EC2 C7gd, M7gd and R7gd metal instances with up to 3.8 TB of local NVMe-based SSD block-level storage have up to 45% improved real-time NVMe storage performance than comparable Graviton2-based instances.
- `aws-sdk-eks` (1.21.0): Add multiple customer error code to handle customer caused failure when managing EKS node groups
- `aws-sdk-guardduty` (1.21.0): Add EC2 support for GuardDuty Runtime Monitoring auto management.
- `aws-sdk-neptunegraph` (1.14.0): Update ImportTaskCancelled waiter to evaluate task state correctly and minor documentation changes.
- `aws-sdk-oam` (1.19.0): This release adds support for sharing AWS::InternetMonitor::Monitor resources.
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.21.0): Amazon QuickSight: Adds support for setting up VPC Endpoint restrictions for accessing QuickSight Website.

March 27th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-batch` (1.22.0): This feature allows AWS Batch to support configuration of imagePullSecrets and allowPrivilegeEscalation for jobs running on EKS
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagent` (1.17.0): This changes introduces metadata documents statistics and also updates the documentation for bedrock agent.
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.17.0): This release introduces filtering support on Retrieve and RetrieveAndGenerate APIs.
- `aws-sdk-elasticache` (1.20.0): Added minimum capacity to  Amazon ElastiCache Serverless. This feature allows customer to ensure minimum capacity even without current load

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-secretsmanager` (1.20.1): Documentation updates for Secrets Manager

March 26th, 2024
================
**New this release:**
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3488](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3488)) Users may now set an endpoint URL from the env or profile file:

    - env: `AWS_ENDPOINT_URL="http://localhost"`
    - profile: `endpoint_url = http://localhost`

    Users may also ignore endpoint URLs sourced from the env and profile files:

    - env: `AWS_IGNORE_CONFIGURED_ENDPOINT_URLS="true"`
    - profile: `ignore_configured_endpoint_urls = true`
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3478](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3478)) `DefaultS3ExpressIdentityProvider` now uses `BehaviorVersion` threaded through from the outer S3 client, instead of always creating `BehaviorVersion::latest()` on the fly.
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3498](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3498)) Fix a bug where a `sigv4-s3express` auth scheme was incorrectly positioned at the front of `auth_scheme_options` and was used when no auth schemes were available for an endpoint.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.16.0): This release adds support to customize prompts sent through the RetrieveAndGenerate API in Agents for Amazon Bedrock.
- `aws-sdk-costexplorer` (1.19.0): Adds support for backfill of cost allocation tags, with new StartCostAllocationTagBackfill and ListCostAllocationTagBackfillHistory API.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.29.0): Documentation updates for Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2).
- `aws-sdk-finspace` (1.21.0): Add new operation delete-kx-cluster-node and add status parameter to list-kx-cluster-node operation.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.19.0): This is a documentation update for Amazon ECS.

March 25th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.21.0): Supporting GitLab and GitLab Self Managed as source types in AWS CodeBuild.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.28.0): Added support for ModifyInstanceMetadataDefaults and GetInstanceMetadataDefaults to set Instance Metadata Service account defaults
- `aws-sdk-emrcontainers` (1.18.0): This release increases the number of supported job template parameters from 20 to 100.
- `aws-sdk-globalaccelerator` (1.18.0): AWS Global Accelerator now supports cross-account sharing for bring your own IP addresses.
- `aws-sdk-medialive` (1.20.0): Exposing TileMedia H265 options
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.29.0): Introduced support for the following new instance types on SageMaker Studio for JupyterLab and CodeEditor applications: m6i, m6id, m7i, c6i, c6id, c7i, r6i, r6id, r7i, and p5

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.18.1): Documentation only update for Amazon ECS.

March 22nd, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-kendra` (1.18.0): Documentation update, March 2024. Corrects some docs for Amazon Kendra.
- `aws-sdk-pricing` (1.19.0): Add ResourceNotFoundException to ListPriceLists and GetPriceListFileUrl APIs
- `aws-sdk-rolesanywhere` (1.18.0): This release relaxes constraints on the durationSeconds request parameter for the *Profile APIs that support it. This parameter can now take on values that go up to 43200.
- `aws-sdk-securityhub` (1.19.0): Added new resource detail object to ASFF, including resource for LastKnownExploitAt

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-firehose` (1.19.1): Updates Amazon Firehose documentation for message regarding Enforcing Tags IAM Policy.

March 20th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-accessanalyzer` (1.19.0): This release adds support for policy validation and external access findings for DynamoDB tables and streams. IAM Access Analyzer helps you author functional and secure resource-based policies and identify cross-account access. Updated service API, documentation, and paginators.
- `aws-sdk-connect` (1.28.0): This release updates the *InstanceStorageConfig APIs to support a new ResourceType: REAL_TIME_CONTACT_ANALYSIS_CHAT_SEGMENTS. Use this resource type to enable streaming for real-time analysis of chat contacts and to associate a Kinesis stream where real-time analysis chat segments will be published.
- `aws-sdk-dynamodb` (1.19.0): This release introduces 3 new APIs ('GetResourcePolicy', 'PutResourcePolicy' and 'DeleteResourcePolicy') and modifies the existing 'CreateTable' API for the resource-based policy support. It also modifies several APIs to accept a 'TableArn' for the 'TableName' parameter.
- `aws-sdk-managedblockchainquery` (1.20.0): AMB Query: update GetTransaction to include transactionId as input
- `aws-sdk-savingsplans` (1.18.0): Introducing the Savings Plans Return feature enabling customers to return their Savings Plans within 7 days of purchase.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.20.1): This release adds support for new webhook events (RELEASED and PRERELEASED) and filter types (TAG_NAME and RELEASE_NAME).

March 19th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudwatchlogs` (1.20.0): Update LogSamples field in Anomaly model to be a list of LogEvent
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.27.0): This release adds the new DescribeMacHosts API operation for getting information about EC2 Mac Dedicated Hosts. Users can now see the latest macOS versions that their underlying Apple Mac can support without needing to be updated.
- `aws-sdk-finspace` (1.20.0): Adding new attributes readWrite and onDemand to dataview models for Database Maintenance operations.
- `aws-sdk-managedblockchainquery` (1.19.0): Introduces a new API for Amazon Managed Blockchain Query: ListFilteredTransactionEvents.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudformation` (1.21.1): Documentation update, March 2024. Corrects some formatting.

March 18th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudformation` (1.21.0): This release supports for a new API ListStackSetAutoDeploymentTargets, which provider auto-deployment configuration as a describable resource. Customers can now view the specific combinations of regions and OUs that are being auto-deployed.
- `aws-sdk-kms` (1.18.0): Adds the ability to use the default policy name by omitting the policyName parameter in calls to PutKeyPolicy and GetKeyPolicy
- `aws-sdk-mediatailor` (1.19.0): This release adds support to allow customers to show different content within a channel depending on metadata associated with the viewer.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.24.0): This release launches the ModifyIntegration API and support for data filtering for zero-ETL Integrations.
- `aws-sdk-s3` (1.20.0): Fix two issues with response root node names.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-timestreamquery` (1.17.1): Documentation updates, March 2024

March 15th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-backup` (1.19.0): This release introduces a boolean attribute ManagedByAWSBackupOnly as part of ListRecoveryPointsByResource api to filter the recovery points based on ownership. This attribute can be used to filter out the recovery points protected by AWSBackup.
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.20.0): AWS CodeBuild now supports overflow behavior on Reserved Capacity.
- `aws-sdk-connect` (1.27.0): This release adds Hierarchy based Access Control fields to Security Profile public APIs and adds support for UserAttributeFilter to SearchUsers API.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.26.0): Add media accelerator and neuron device information on the describe instance types API.
- `aws-sdk-kinesisanalyticsv2` (1.18.0): Support for Flink 1.18 in Managed Service for Apache Flink
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.28.0): Adds m6i, m6id, m7i, c6i, c6id, c7i, r6i r6id, r7i, p5 instance type support to Sagemaker Notebook Instances and miscellaneous wording fixes for previous Sagemaker documentation.
- `aws-sdk-workspacesthinclient` (1.16.0): Removed unused parameter kmsKeyArn from UpdateDeviceRequest

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-s3` (1.19.1): Documentation updates for Amazon S3.

March 14th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-ec2instanceconnect` (1.17.0): This release includes a new exception type "SerialConsoleSessionUnsupportedException" for SendSerialConsoleSSHPublicKey API.
- `aws-sdk-fis` (1.17.0): This release adds support for previewing target resources before running a FIS experiment. It also adds resource ARNs for actions, experiments, and experiment templates to API responses.
- `aws-sdk-timestreaminfluxdb` (1.0.0): This is the initial SDK release for Amazon Timestream for InfluxDB. Amazon Timestream for InfluxDB is a new time-series database engine that makes it easy for application developers and DevOps teams to run InfluxDB databases on AWS for near real-time time-series applications using open source APIs.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-amplify` (1.18.0): Documentation updates for Amplify. Identifies the APIs available only to apps created using Amplify Gen 1.
- `aws-sdk-elasticloadbalancingv2` (1.18.0): This release allows you to configure HTTP client keep-alive duration for communication between clients and Application Load Balancers.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.23.0): Updates Amazon RDS documentation for EBCDIC collation for RDS for Db2.
- `aws-sdk-secretsmanager` (1.19.0): Doc only update for Secrets Manager

March 13th, 2024
================
**New this release:**
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3416](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3416), @jackkleeman) EKS Pod Identity is now supported as part of the default ECS credential provider.
- :tada: ([aws-sdk-rust#1075](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1075), [aws-sdk-rust#1080](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1080), [smithy-rs#3451](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3451)) Add support for Lambda's `InvokeWithResponseStreaming` and Bedrock Agent Runtime's `InvokeAgent` operations.
- :tada: ([aws-sdk-rust#703](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/703), [smithy-rs#3453](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3453)) Added support for SSO bearer token authentication. The aws-sdk-codecatalyst crate can now send requests without erroring.
- :tada: ([aws-sdk-rust#992](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/992), [smithy-rs#3465](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3465)) Add support for S3 Express One Zone. See [the user guide](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/discussions/1091) for more details.
- ([smithy-rs#3465](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3465), [smithy-rs#3477](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3477)) `aws_sigv4::http_request::settigns::SigningSettings` adds a new setting `session_token_name_override` to allow for an alternative session token name for SigV4 signing.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-ivsrealtime` (1.16.0): adds support for multiple new composition layout configuration options (grid, pip)
- `aws-sdk-kinesisanalyticsv2` (1.16.0): Support new RuntimeEnvironmentUpdate parameter within UpdateApplication API allowing callers to change the Flink version upon which their application runs.
- `aws-sdk-s3` (1.18.0): This release makes the default option for S3 on Outposts request signing to use the SigV4A algorithm when using AWS Common Runtime (CRT).

**Contributors**
Thank you for your contributions! ❤

March 12th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-connect` (1.24.0): This release increases MaxResults limit to 500 in request for SearchUsers, SearchQueues and SearchRoutingProfiles APIs of Amazon Connect.
- `aws-sdk-kafka` (1.16.0): Added support for specifying the starting position of topic replication in MSK-Replicator.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudformation` (1.18.1): CloudFormation documentation update for March, 2024
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.23.1): Documentation updates for Amazon EC2.
- `aws-sdk-ssm` (1.17.1): March 2024 doc-only updates for Systems Manager.

March 11th, 2024
================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-codestarconnections` (1.17.0): Added a sync configuration enum to disable publishing of deployment status to source providers (PublishDeploymentStatus). Added a sync configuration enum (TriggerStackUpdateOn) to only trigger changes.
- `aws-sdk-mediapackagev2` (1.16.0): This release enables customers to safely update their MediaPackage v2 channel groups, channels and origin endpoints using entity tags.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-elasticache` (1.16.1): Revisions to API text that are now to be carried over to SDK text, changing usages of "SFO" in code examples to "us-west-1", and some other typos.

March 8th, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-batch` (1.18.0): This release adds JobStateTimeLimitActions setting to the Job Queue API. It allows you to configure an action Batch can take for a blocking job in front of the queue after the defined period of time. The new parameter applies for ECS, EKS, and FARGATE Job Queues.
- `aws-sdk-cloudtrail` (1.17.0): Added exceptions to CreateTrail, DescribeTrails, and ListImportFailures APIs.
- `aws-sdk-cognitoidentityprovider` (1.18.0): Add ConcurrentModificationException to SetUserPoolMfaConfig
- `aws-sdk-guardduty` (1.17.0): Add RDS Provisioned and Serverless Usage types
- `aws-sdk-transfer` (1.17.0): Added DES_EDE3_CBC to the list of supported encryption algorithms for messages sent with an AS2 connector.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.13.1): Documentation update for Bedrock Runtime Agent
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.17.1): This release adds support for a new webhook event: PULL_REQUEST_CLOSED.

March 7th, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-appconfig` (1.16.0): AWS AppConfig now supports dynamic parameters, which enhance the functionality of AppConfig Extensions by allowing you to provide parameter values to your Extensions at the time you deploy your configuration.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.23.0): This release adds an optional parameter to RegisterImage and CopyImage APIs to support tagging AMIs at the time of creation.
- `aws-sdk-grafana` (1.16.0): Adds support for the new GrafanaToken as part of the Amazon Managed Grafana Enterprise plugins upgrade to associate your AWS account with a Grafana Labs account.
- `aws-sdk-paymentcryptographydata` (1.16.0): AWS Payment Cryptography EMV Decrypt Feature  Release
- `aws-sdk-wafv2` (1.18.0): You can increase the max request body inspection size for some regional resources. The size setting is in the web ACL association config. Also, the AWSManagedRulesBotControlRuleSet EnableMachineLearning setting now takes a Boolean instead of a primitive boolean type, for languages like Java.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-lambda` (1.15.1): Documentation updates for AWS Lambda
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.21.1): Updates Amazon RDS documentation for io2 storage for Multi-AZ DB clusters
- `aws-sdk-snowball` (1.15.1): Doc-only update for change to EKS-Anywhere ordering.
- `aws-sdk-workspaces` (1.15.1): Added note for user decoupling

March 6th, 2024
===============
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-imagebuilder` (1.16.0): Add PENDING status to Lifecycle Execution resource status. Add StartTime and EndTime to ListLifecycleExecutionResource API response.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.21.0): Updated the input of CreateDBCluster and ModifyDBCluster to support setting CA certificates. Updated the output of DescribeDBCluster to show current CA certificate setting value.
- `aws-sdk-verifiedpermissions` (1.17.0): Deprecating details in favor of configuration for GetIdentitySource and ListIdentitySources APIs.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-dynamodb` (1.16.1): Doc only updates for DynamoDB documentation
- `aws-sdk-mwaa` (1.17.1): Amazon MWAA adds support for Apache Airflow v2.8.1.
- `aws-sdk-redshift` (1.16.1): Update for documentation only. Covers port ranges, definition updates for data sharing, and definition updates to cluster-snapshot documentation.

- `aws-sdk-organizations` (1.17.0): This release contains an endpoint addition

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-apigateway` (1.15.1): Documentation updates for Amazon API Gateway
- `aws-sdk-chatbot` (1.2.1): Minor update to documentation.

February 29th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-docdbelastic` (1.16.0): Launched Elastic Clusters Readable Secondaries, Start/Stop, Configurable Shard Instance count, Automatic Backups and Snapshot Copying
- `aws-sdk-eks` (1.17.0): Added support for new AL2023 AMIs to the supported AMITypes.
- `aws-sdk-lexmodelsv2` (1.17.0): This release makes AMAZON.QnAIntent generally available in Amazon Lex. This generative AI feature leverages large language models available through Amazon Bedrock to automate frequently asked questions (FAQ) experience for end-users.
- `aws-sdk-migrationhuborchestrator` (1.16.0): Adds new CreateTemplate, UpdateTemplate and DeleteTemplate APIs.
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.17.0): TooltipTarget for Combo chart visuals; ColumnConfiguration limit increase to 2000; Documentation Update
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.25.0): Adds support for ModelDataSource in Model Packages to support unzipped models. Adds support to specify SourceUri for models which allows registration of models without mandating a container for hosting. Using SourceUri, customers can decouple the model from hosting information during registration.
- `aws-sdk-securitylake` (1.16.0): Add capability to update the Data Lake's MetaStoreManager Role in order to perform required data lake updates to use Iceberg table format in their data lake or update the role for any other reason.

February 28th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-batch` (1.17.0): This release adds Batch support for configuration of multicontainer jobs in ECS, Fargate, and EKS. This support is available for all types of jobs, including both array jobs and multi-node parallel jobs.
- `aws-sdk-bedrockagentruntime` (1.13.0): This release adds support to override search strategy performed by the Retrieve and RetrieveAndGenerate APIs for Amazon Bedrock Agents
- `aws-sdk-costexplorer` (1.16.0): This release introduces the new API 'GetApproximateUsageRecords', which retrieves estimated usage records for hourly granularity or resource-level data at daily granularity.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.22.0): This release increases the range of MaxResults for GetNetworkInsightsAccessScopeAnalysisFindings to 1,000.
- `aws-sdk-iot` (1.18.0): This release reduces the maximum results returned per query invocation from 500 to 100 for the SearchIndex API. This change has no implications as long as the API is invoked until the nextToken is NULL.
- `aws-sdk-wafv2` (1.17.0): AWS WAF now supports configurable time windows for request aggregation with rate-based rules. Customers can now select time windows of 1 minute, 2 minutes or 10 minutes, in addition to the previously supported 5 minutes.

February 26th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-drs` (1.16.0): Added volume status to DescribeSourceServer replicated volumes.
- `aws-sdk-kafkaconnect` (1.15.0): Adds support for tagging, with new TagResource, UntagResource and ListTagsForResource APIs to manage tags and updates to existing APIs to allow tag on create. This release also adds support for the new DeleteWorkerConfiguration API.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.19.0): This release adds support for gp3 data volumes for Multi-AZ DB Clusters.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-apigateway` (1.14.1): Documentation updates for Amazon API Gateway.

February 22nd, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-iotevents` (1.15.0): Increase the maximum length of descriptions for Inputs, Detector Models, and Alarm Models
- `aws-sdk-lookoutequipment` (1.16.0): This release adds a field exposing model quality to read APIs for models. It also adds a model quality field to the API response when creating an inference scheduler.
- `aws-sdk-medialive` (1.16.0): MediaLive now supports the ability to restart pipelines in a running channel.
- `aws-sdk-ssm` (1.16.0): This release adds support for sharing Systems Manager parameters with other AWS accounts.

**Breaking Changes:**
- :bug::warning: ([smithy-rs#3405](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3405), [smithy-rs#3400](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3400), [smithy-rs#3258](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3258)) Fix bug where timeout settings where not merged properly. This will add a default connect timeout of 3.1s seconds for most clients.

    [**For more details see the long-form changelog discussion**](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/discussions/3408).

**New this release:**
- :tada: ([smithy-rs#3385](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3385), [aws-sdk-rust#1031](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1031)) It is now possible to send customized presigned requests. You can now call `.customize().<customizations>.presigned(...).await`. Previously, only normal requests supported customization.
- ([smithy-rs#3355](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3355)) The types in the aws-http crate were moved into aws-runtime. Deprecated type aliases were put in place to point to the new locations.
- ([aws-sdk-rust#977](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/977), [smithy-rs#3365](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3365), [smithy-rs#3373](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3373)) Add `try_into_http1x` and `try_from_http1x` to Request and Response container types.
- ([smithy-rs#3336](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3336), [smithy-rs#3391](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3391), @iampkmone) Added impl `Display` to Enums.
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3322](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3322)) Retry classifiers will now be sorted by priority. This change only affects requests
    that are retried. Some requests that were previously been classified as transient
    errors may now be classified as throttling errors.

    If you were

    - configuring multiple custom retry classifiers
    - that would disagree on how to classify a response
    - that have differing priorities

    you may see a behavior change in that classification for the same response is now
    dependent on the classifier priority instead of the order in which the classifier
    was added.
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3402](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3402)) Cap the maximum jitter fraction for credentials cache refresh buffer time to 0.5. It was previously 1.0, and if the fraction was randomly set to 1.0, it was equivalent to disregarding the buffer time for cache refresh.
- :bug: ([smithy-rs#3387](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3387)) Retain the SSO token cache between calls to `provide_credentials` when using IAM Identity Center SSO via the AWS config file.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-firehose` (1.16.0): This release updates a few Firehose related APIs.
- `aws-sdk-lambda` (1.14.0): Add .NET 8 (dotnet8) Runtime support to AWS Lambda.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-dynamodb` (1.15.0): Publishing quick fix for doc only update.

**Contributors**
Thank you for your contributions! ❤

February 19th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-amplify` (1.14.0): This release contains API changes that enable users to configure their Amplify domains with their own custom SSL/TLS certificate.
- `aws-sdk-chatbot` (1.0.0): This release adds support for AWS Chatbot. You can now monitor, operate, and troubleshoot your AWS resources with interactive ChatOps using the AWS SDK.
- `aws-sdk-mediatailor` (1.14.0): MediaTailor: marking #AdBreak.OffsetMillis as required.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-config` (1.14.1): Documentation updates for the AWS Config CLI
- `aws-sdk-ivs` (1.14.1): Changed description for latencyMode in Create/UpdateChannel and Channel/ChannelSummary.
- `aws-sdk-keyspaces` (1.14.1): Documentation updates for Amazon Keyspaces

February 16th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-emr` (1.15.0): adds fine grained control over Unhealthy Node Replacement to Amazon ElasticMapReduce
- `aws-sdk-firehose` (1.15.0): This release adds support for Data Message Extraction for decompressed CloudWatch logs, and to use a custom file extension or time zone for S3 destinations.
- `aws-sdk-sns` (1.14.0): This release marks phone numbers as sensitive inputs.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-connectparticipant` (1.14.1): Doc only update to GetTranscript API reference guide to inform users about presence of events in the chat transcript.
- `aws-sdk-lambda` (1.13.1): Documentation-only updates for Lambda to clarify a number of existing actions and properties.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.16.1): Doc only update for a valid option in DB parameter group

February 15th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-artifact` (1.0.0): This is the initial SDK release for AWS Artifact. AWS Artifact provides on-demand access to compliance and third-party compliance reports. This release includes access to List and Get reports, along with their metadata. This release also includes access to AWS Artifact notifications settings.
- `aws-sdk-codepipeline` (1.14.0): Add ability to override timeout on action level.
- `aws-sdk-guardduty` (1.14.0): Marked fields IpAddressV4, PrivateIpAddress, Email as Sensitive.
- `aws-sdk-healthlake` (1.14.0): This release adds a new response parameter, JobProgressReport, to the DescribeFHIRImportJob and ListFHIRImportJobs API operation. JobProgressReport provides details on the progress of the import job on the server.
- `aws-sdk-opensearch` (1.17.0): Adds additional supported instance types.
- `aws-sdk-polly` (1.14.0): Amazon Polly adds 1 new voice - Burcu (tr-TR)
- `aws-sdk-sagemaker` (1.22.0): This release adds a new API UpdateClusterSoftware for SageMaker HyperPod. This API allows users to patch HyperPod clusters with latest platform softwares.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-detective` (1.13.1): Doc only updates for content enhancement
- `aws-sdk-secretsmanager` (1.15.1): Doc only update for Secrets Manager

February 14th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-controltower` (1.14.0): Adds support for new Baseline and EnabledBaseline APIs for automating multi-account governance.
- `aws-sdk-lookoutequipment` (1.14.0): This feature allows customers to see pointwise model diagnostics results for their models.
- `aws-sdk-qbusiness` (1.11.0): This release adds the metadata-boosting feature, which allows customers to easily fine-tune the underlying ranking of retrieved RAG passages in order to optimize Q&A answer relevance. It also adds new feedback reasons for the PutFeedback API.

February 13th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-lightsail` (1.15.0): This release adds support to upgrade the major version of a database.
- `aws-sdk-marketplacecatalog` (1.16.0): AWS Marketplace Catalog API now supports setting intent on requests
- `aws-sdk-resourceexplorer2` (1.14.0): Resource Explorer now uses newly supported IPv4 'amazonaws.com' endpoints by default.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-securitylake` (1.13.1): Documentation updates for Security Lake

February 13th, 2024
===================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-appsync` (1.16.0): Adds support for new options on GraphqlAPIs, Resolvers and  Data Sources for emitting Amazon CloudWatch metrics for enhanced monitoring of AppSync APIs.
- `aws-sdk-cloudwatch` (1.15.0): This release add PutMetricData compression in the model, however, the Rust SDK does not yet support this behavior. This is tracked in https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1068
- `aws-sdk-neptunegraph` (1.8.0): Adding a new option "parameters" for data plane api ExecuteQuery to support running parameterized query via SDK.
- `aws-sdk-route53domains` (1.14.0): This release adds bill contact support for RegisterDomain, TransferDomain, UpdateDomainContact and GetDomainDetail API.

February 9th, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-batch` (1.14.0): This feature allows Batch to support configuration of repository credentials for jobs running on ECS
- `aws-sdk-braket` (1.15.0): Creating a job will result in DeviceOfflineException when using an offline device, and DeviceRetiredException when using a retired device.
- `aws-sdk-costoptimizationhub` (1.12.0): Adding includeMemberAccounts field to the response of ListEnrollmentStatuses API.
- `aws-sdk-iot` (1.15.0): This release allows AWS IoT Core users to enable Online Certificate Status Protocol (OCSP) Stapling for TLS X.509 Server Certificates when creating and updating AWS IoT Domain Configurations with Custom Domain.
- `aws-sdk-pricing` (1.14.0): Add Throttling Exception to all APIs.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-amp` (1.13.1): Overall documentation updates.
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.14.1): Documentation only update for Amazon ECS.

February 9th, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-codepipeline` (1.13.0): Add ability to execute pipelines with new parallel & queued execution modes and add support for triggers with filtering on branches and file paths.
- `aws-sdk-quicksight` (1.14.0): General Interactions for Visuals; Waterfall Chart Color Configuration; Documentation Update
- `aws-sdk-workspaces` (1.13.0): This release introduces User-Decoupling feature. This feature allows Workspaces Core customers to provision workspaces without providing users. CreateWorkspaces and DescribeWorkspaces APIs will now take a new optional parameter "WorkspaceName".

February 6th, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-appsync` (1.14.0): Support for environment variables in AppSync GraphQL APIs
- `aws-sdk-cloudwatchlogs` (1.14.0): This release adds a new field, logGroupArn, to the response of the logs:DescribeLogGroups action.
- `aws-sdk-elasticsearch` (1.14.0): This release adds clear visibility to the customers on the changes that they make on the domain.
- `aws-sdk-opensearch` (1.15.0): This release adds clear visibility to the customers on the changes that they make on the domain.
- `aws-sdk-wafv2` (1.13.0): You can now delete an API key that you've created for use with your CAPTCHA JavaScript integration API.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.13.1): This release is a documentation only update to address customer issues.

February 1st, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cognitoidentityprovider` (1.14.0): Added CreateIdentityProvider and UpdateIdentityProvider details for new SAML IdP features
- `aws-sdk-ivs` (1.13.0): This release introduces a new resource Playback Restriction Policy which can be used to geo-restrict or domain-restrict channel stream playback when associated with a channel.  New APIs to support this resource were introduced in the form of Create/Delete/Get/Update/List.
- `aws-sdk-managedblockchainquery` (1.13.0): This release adds support for transactions that have not reached finality. It also removes support for the status property from the response of the GetTransaction operation. You can use the confirmationStatus and executionStatus properties to determine the status of the transaction.
- `aws-sdk-mediaconvert` (1.14.0): This release includes support for broadcast-mixed audio description tracks.
- `aws-sdk-neptunegraph` (1.6.0): Adding new APIs in SDK for Amazon Neptune Analytics. These APIs include operations to execute, cancel, list queries and get the graph summary.

January 31st, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-cloudformation` (1.14.0): CloudFormation IaC generator allows you to scan existing resources in your account and select resources to generate a template for a new or existing CloudFormation stack.
- `aws-sdk-elasticloadbalancingv2` (1.13.0): This release enables unhealthy target draining intervals for Network Load Balancers.
- `aws-sdk-glue` (1.15.0): Update page size limits for GetJobRuns and GetTriggers APIs.
- `aws-sdk-ssm` (1.13.0): This release adds an optional Duration parameter to StateManager Associations. This allows customers to specify how long an apply-only-on-cron association execution should run. Once the specified Duration is out all the ongoing cancellable commands or automations are cancelled.

January 29th, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-autoscaling` (1.13.0): EC2 Auto Scaling customers who use attribute based instance-type selection can now intuitively define their Spot instances price protection limit as a percentage of the lowest priced On-Demand instance type.
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.18.0): EC2 Fleet customers who use attribute based instance-type selection can now intuitively define their Spot instances price protection limit as a percentage of the lowest priced On-Demand instance type.
- `aws-sdk-mwaa` (1.14.0): This release adds MAINTENANCE environment status for Amazon MWAA environments.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.15.0): Introduced support for the InsufficientDBInstanceCapacityFault error in the RDS RestoreDBClusterFromSnapshot and RestoreDBClusterToPointInTime API methods. This provides enhanced error handling, ensuring a more robust experience.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-comprehend` (1.12.1): Comprehend PII analysis now supports Spanish input documents.
- `aws-sdk-snowball` (1.12.1): Modified description of createaddress to include direction to add path when providing a JSON file.

==================
**New this release:**
- :tada: ([aws-sdk-rust#703](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/703), [smithy-rs#3379](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3379)) Add support for `[sso-session]` in AWS config file for AWS Identity Center SSO credentials. Note that this does not include support for AWS Builder ID SSO sessions for services such as Code Catalyst (these lack the `sso_account_id` and `sso_role_name` fields in the profile config). Support for AWS Builder IDs is still being tracked in https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/703.
- ([smithy-rs#3355](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3355)) The types in the aws-http crate were moved into aws-runtime. Deprecated type aliases were put in place to point to the new locations.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-acmpca` (1.12.0): AWS Private CA now supports an option to omit the CDP extension from issued certificates, when CRL revocation is enabled.
- `aws-sdk-lightsail` (1.13.0): This release adds support for IPv6-only instance plans.

January 24th, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.16.0): Introduced a new clientToken request parameter on CreateNetworkAcl and CreateRouteTable APIs. The clientToken parameter allows idempotent operations on the APIs.
- `aws-sdk-outposts` (1.12.0): DeviceSerialNumber parameter is now optional in StartConnection API
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.13.0): This release adds support for Aurora Limitless Database.
- `aws-sdk-storagegateway` (1.12.0): Add DeprecationDate and SoftwareVersion to response of ListGateways.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.12.1): Documentation updates for Amazon ECS.

January 22nd, 2024
==================
**New this release:**
- :tada: ([aws-sdk-rust#1041](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/1041), [smithy-rs#3366](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3366)) Add `apply_to_request_http1x` to `aws-sigv4` to enable signing http = 1.0 requests.
- ([smithy-rs#3318](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3318)) `EndpointPrefix` and `apply_endpoint` moved from aws-smithy-http to aws-smithy-runtime-api so that is in a stable (1.x) crate. A deprecated type alias was left in place with a note showing the new location.
- :bug: ([aws-sdk-rust#901](https://github.com/awslabs/aws-sdk-rust/issues/901), [smithy-rs#3363](https://github.com/smithy-lang/smithy-rs/issues/3363)) Fix bug where overriding the credentials at the operation level failed if credentials were already set.

**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-appconfigdata` (1.11.0): Fix FIPS Endpoints in aws-us-gov.
- `aws-sdk-cloudfrontkeyvaluestore` (1.11.0): This release improves upon the DescribeKeyValueStore API by returning two additional fields, Status of the KeyValueStore and the FailureReason in case of failures during creation of KeyValueStore.
- `aws-sdk-connectcases` (1.12.0): This release adds the ability to view audit history on a case and introduces a new parameter, performedBy, for CreateCase and UpdateCase API's.
- `aws-sdk-ecs` (1.12.0): This release adds support for Transport Layer Security (TLS) and Configurable Timeout to ECS Service Connect. TLS facilitates privacy and data security for inter-service communications, while Configurable Timeout allows customized per-request timeout and idle timeout for Service Connect services.
- `aws-sdk-finspace` (1.13.0): Allow customer to set zip default through command line arguments.
- `aws-sdk-rds` (1.12.0): Introduced support for the InsufficientDBInstanceCapacityFault error in the RDS CreateDBCluster API method. This provides enhanced error handling, ensuring a more robust experience when creating database clusters with insufficient instance capacity.

**Service Documentation:**
- `aws-sdk-cloud9` (1.12.0): Doc-only update around removing AL1 from list of available AMIs for Cloud9
- `aws-sdk-ec2` (1.15.0): Documentation updates for Amazon EC2.
- `aws-sdk-organizations` (1.11.0): Doc only update for quota increase change

January 19th, 2024
==================
**Service Features:**
- `aws-sdk-athena` (1.11.0): Introducing new NotebookS3LocationUri parameter to Athena ImportNotebook API. Payload is no longer required and either Payload or NotebookS3LocationUri needs to be provided (not both) for a successful ImportNotebook API call. If both are provided, an InvalidRequestException will be thrown.
- `aws-sdk-codebuild` (1.12.0): Release CodeBuild Reserved Capacity feature
- `aws-sdk-dynamodb` (1.11.0): This release adds support for including ApproximateCreationDateTimePrecision configurations in EnableKinesisStreamingDestination API, adds the same as an optional field in the response of DescribeKinesisStreamingDestination, and adds support for a new UpdateKinesisStreamingDestination API.
- `aws-sdk-qconnect` (1.11.0): Increased Quick Response name max length to 100
